Description
-----------

  Anime-X is an electronic magazine which features:

  - an A-Z listing of over 100 erotic anime titles
  - articles of computer games and interactive erotica
  - adult anime PC-CDROM games

  This is a production that contains major rework and enhancements over its
  predecessor `Anime-V' (released in 01.05.96).

  Anime-X was designed to fit onto a single 880k floppy disk, therefore
  please note that there are no hentai or pornographic images on the disk.

Disclaimer
----------

  Anime-X is freely distributable.

Requirements
------------

  Anime-X requires:

  - AmigaDos 2.0+
  - 68020
  - 2MB ChipRAM

  For Workbench users:  The memory exception has been removed in order for
  Anime-X  to  run,  but  you  still  need  at  least 1.2Mb of free ChipRAM
  otherwise Anime-X will not run properly.

  Anime-X is compatible with the WinUAE Amiga emulator.  It runs fine on a
  PII 333 and Athlon 650.

Harddrive Users
---------------

  To  run  Anime-X  from your HD simply copy Anime-X to the a directory and
  copy the directory in Fonts to SYS:FONTS/.

